<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 16 at 5:30PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong convective shower will impact portions of northeastern
McCone County through 600 PM MDT...
At 529 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong convective shower
9 miles southwest of Vida, or 22 miles south of Wolf Point, moving
southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern McCone
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
